                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Press Release Issued by the White House on July 31, 1940</hi>
                    <note n="15" type="source" xml:id="d138fn15">Reprinted from Department of State,
                            <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, August 3, 1940 (vol. <hi
                            rend="smallcaps">iii</hi>, No. 58), p. 94.</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-head" calendar="gregorian"
                        when="1940-07-31">July 31, 1940</date>
                </dateline>
                <p>Col. R. L. Maxwell, Administrator of Export Control, recommends, and the
                    President approves, the issuance of the following announcement: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>In the interests of the national defense the export of aviation gasoline
                            is being limited to nations of the Western Hemisphere, except where such
                            gasoline is required elsewhere for the operations of American-owned
                            companies.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
            </div>
